Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the
@rigatoni pasta{180%g}.

Halve, peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped).

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When boiling, add the rigatoni to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook
until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{for drizzling} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{for frying} in a large #frying pan{} on high
heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and
@sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the frying pan and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook until browned all over, ~{4-5%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

Lower the heat to medium, then add the onion to the frying pan and stir-fry
until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When the onion has softened, add the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g} to the
frying pan. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @red wine jus paste{15%g}, @Worcester sauce{15%g}, @mixed herbs{1%sachet},
@sugar{1%tsp} and @water for the sauce{200%ml}. Stir to combine.

> TIP: If your red wine jus paste has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water
> for 1 min.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat so the sauce simmers gently. Cook until
the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked and the sauce has thickened, stir through the
@butter{20%g} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} until melted.
When the sauce is ready, stir through the cooked rigatoni. Toss well to combine.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if
the sauce is a little thick.

Share the chicken chasseur style pasta between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese to finish.

Enjoy!